## Description
The**&nbsp;Batch FTP ingress&nbsp;**resource&nbsp;allows to retrieve files from an FTP server in a Batch workflow.

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant** on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Customer**

**Username**

Enter the FTP username of the user who will upload the input files for this ingress

**Trigger**

**Policy**

Select one of the trigger policy options:

- **Transfer*** (default)*: The workflow will be triggered when a matching file is loaded to the FTP server.

- **Rename**: The workflow will be triggered when a file is renamed to a matching pattern.

> Important

The options are mutually exclusive.

**Files**

**Input folder**

Enter the remote path on the filesystem of the FTP server from which&nbsp;to retrieve files.

> Note

This is a relative path to the user's home folder on the FTP server, that must be provided by the Client in the setup phase.

The specified folder must already exist on the FTP server.

**Include files by pattern**

Enter one or more filename&nbsp;patterns&nbsp;to filter the files to retrieve from the FTP server (for example: **.zip*) and press *Enter* to confirm.

> Tip

You may specify multiple file pattern rules to retrieve input files with multiple extensions. If a file matches at least one rule, then a new job is triggered. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

This field supports regular expressions using the * wildcard character. Moreover, it supports complex rules using glob syntax.

> Important

If an input file does not match any of the specified file pattern rules, or if the patterns specified in two different Batch FTP Ingress resources linked to the same workflow overlap, no job is triggered.

**Exclude files by pattern**

See **Include files by pattern**. This option allows to exclude filename patterns when retrieving files from the FTP server.

**Deduplicate inputs by filename**

Select this option to ignore all inputs with the same filename except the first one.

> Deduplication window

The time window for deduplication depends on the configured retention period for job inputs.

This retention period can be configured on tenant level. After its expiration, the job information is still visible in the Batch Jobs portal, but the input data is removed from storage.

**Deduplicate inputs by content**

Select this option to ignore all inputs with the same content except the first one.

> Deduplication window

The time window for deduplication depends on the configured retention period for job inputs.

This retention period can be configured on tenant level. After its expiration, the job information is still visible in the Batch Jobs portal, but the input data is removed from storage.

**Workflow**

**Resource**

Select the Batch Workflows resource that will be triggered by this ingress.

> Important

If the selected workflow has not been deployed on the selected tenant, a warning message is displayed.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
